<br>
I have recently solo'd the AC (woohoo!), and that went pretty well with chain-summoning.  So, I thought I'd give a platinum-laden SG a shot.<br>
<br>
Sicked my buffed up earth pet at the giant, and I malised him.  Nuked 2-3 times with Cinder Bolt, they all hit for full damage.  Med.<br>
<br>
Time for another earth pet, sick him in.  DS the pet (burnout too?  I forget now).  Med a min or two.  Time for another earth pet.  Sick him in.  But here's where it went bad... the SG ignored my pet and beat the living crap out of me.  My pet got him off me after a bit, but I was down to 1/8 of a bub of life, so I gated away regardless.<br>
<br>
I think I had about 1.5 bubs of mana left in the end, so I'm not sure nuking more would have been healthy.  The giant was at about 25% health.  I would have taken at least 2 Cinder Bolts to finish him off.<br>
<br>
What am I doing wrong here?  I know necros can solo SGs at 29 with difficulty, and with ease at 34.  I should definitely be able to solo an SG at 40.  Please provide feedback.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Balasarius NoxDominus<br>
40th Circle Mage<br>
Seventh Hammer<br>
